                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/595: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-03T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s April 29, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>Your April 30, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>Keep close watch on situation and cable Department developments. The Department
                    does not wish to be placed in the position where it can be criticised for
                    failure to urge upon President Chamorro the careful fulfillment of his duty to
                    prevent expeditions being organized on territory of Nicaragua, and his duty to
                    remain strictly neutral in any struggle between Tinoco and his opponents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
